snippet.textDisplay: When Nipsey Hussle died I never knew who was he. Thought he was some typical rapper dying, until I see what he actually did. It made me regret not knowing who he was, like this guy was an inspiration to the community and brought not only gangs but also the LAPD. Though a month after he died, I went to a supermarket and a guy had a shirt of Nipsey Hussle. Remind you he has tats on his head, Idgaf and say to him, "hey bro I like your shirt man", he thank me and we went personal, how he was raised in the gang in Irvine, how his 2 brothers was killed, one died when he was 9. That hit me man, but then he also met "Nipsey Hussle" in person as well. Like man I told him straight up what I thought who he was at first. We understood but we cross paths since then. I hope that guy has peace for the future and also his 2 brothers.
